  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Prep your ingredients. Take your mint and coriander. With a knife, separate the stalks and the leaves. Finely chop the stalks of both but keep them separate. Finely chop your coriander and mint leaves."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Peel your ginger and chop into small matchsticks. Finely slice 1 red chilli and 4 spring onions. Measure out 4 tbsp of fish sauce."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "At this point, get 300g of rice on. Rinse the rice and add it to a pan with 2 times the amount of boiling water. Cook without a lid until the water has been absorbed."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In a large wok or frying pan, add a splash of olive oil and then add your pork mince. Fry on a high heat, breaking it up with a wooden spoon. As the pork starts to caramelise, remove it from the wok and set it aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In the same wok, add a splash more oil. Add your ginger, red chilli, mint and coriander stalks, spring onions and 2 tsp of lemongrass puree."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Keep mixing your larb base. Once it starts to catch on the pan, pour in your fish sauce and squeeze in the juice of a lime. Mix it together, and then reintroduce the pork mince. Stir."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add your rice spoon by spoon. Once all the rice and pork is folded together, add your coriander and mint leaves. Mix together. Remove the larb from the heat."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Serve the larb in crispy lettuce leaves and enjoy!"
    }
  ],
